{"users": {"1": {"id": "default", "health_mode": "Diabetic Friendly", "created_at": "2026-05-23T05:57:45.418922", "updated_at": "2026-05-23T05:57:45.418936"}}, "scans": {"1": {"id": "5ada287a-bf10-4d5f-8647-d76e69e3b199", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-23T05:57:45.421626", "corrected_text": "Oats, Sugar, Palm Oil, Artificial Color, Tartrazine", "score": 75, "grade": "B", "explanation": "Oats are high in fiber (+10), but contains sugar (-10), palm oil (-10), and artificial colors (-5).", "alternative": {"name": "Homemade Roasted Oats", "recipe": "Roast rolled oats with healthy nuts."}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Oats are high in fiber", "impact": 10}, {"reason": "Contains added sugars", "impact": -10}, {"reason": "Contains palm oil", "impact": -10}, {"reason": "Contains artificial color", "impact": -5}]}, "2": {"id": "574b25cf-8411-4386-97d5-c514255fc552", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-24T03:59:10.527383", "corrected_text": "bleach, natural flavor, sugar", "score": 100, "grade": "S", "explanation": "This product's score is based on its ingredient profile. Please review the score breakdown for details.", "alternative": {"name": "AI Assistant Busy", "recipe": "Our AI is currently taking a short break (rate limit). Please try again in a few moments for a custom recipe!"}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Standard ingredients, no major health risks or benefits detected.", "impact": 0}]}, "3": {"id": "8085044e-fd41-4a26-9c01-cdaa3a8341cf", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-24T04:15:25.610577", "corrected_text": "Ingredients: Rolled Oats (25.1%), Candied Fruit and Nut (24%)\n{Candied Cranberry (14%), Almonds (10%)}, Sugar, Oat Flour (10.7%),\nEdible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein), Rice (4.2%), Whole Wheat (3.9%),\nRice Flour (2.7%), Liquid Glucose, Corn Flour (1.8%), Honey, Malt Extract,\nWheat Bran (0.6%), Wheat Flour (0.5%), Iodized Salt, Dextrose,\nBarley Flour (0.1%), Vitamins, Raising Agent (INS 500ii),\nMinerals, Antioxidant (INS 320)\nCONTAINS ADDED FLAVOURS (NATURE IDENTICAL AND\nARTIFICIAL CREAM FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES)\nCONTAINS GLUTEN, ALMONDS.\nMAY CONTAIN TRACES OF SOY AND MILK.", "score": 100, "grade": "S", "explanation": "This 100/100 (Grade S) score means the product uses standard, common ingredients. No ingredients were found that pose major health risks, nor are there specific components offering significant health benefits. It indicates a neutral ingredient profile, free from major concerns.", "alternative": {"name": "Moong Dal Khichdi", "recipe": "1. Rinse rice and moong dal. 2. Cook with water, turmeric, and salt. 3. Simmer until soft."}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Standard ingredients, no major health risks or benefits detected.", "impact": 0}]}, "4": {"id": "b53a1445-4bad-437e-a4da-ac3786c91c8c", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-24T05:11:38.701090", "corrected_text": "INGREDIENTS:\nREFINED WHEAT FLOUR (43%), WHOLE WHEAT\nFLOUR (20%), EDIBLE VEGETABLE OIL, SUGAR,\nWHEAT BRAN (4.7%), MILK SOLIDS, LIQUID\nGLUCOSE, CEREAL PRODUCTS, RAISING\nAGENTS [500(ii), 503(ii)], EDIBLE COMMON SALT,\nEMULSIFIERS [322, 472e, 471 & 481(i)], MALT\nEXTRACT AND DOUGH CONDITIONER (223).\n(Numbers in brackets as per International Numbering System)\nCONTAINS ADDED FLAVOURS -\n(ARTIFICIAL FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES -\nVANILLA, CEREAL & MILK)\n\nSTORE IN A COOL, HYGIENIC AND DRY PLACE\nTRANSFER CONTENTS TO A CLEAN AND TIGHT\nCONTAINER ONCE OPENED.\n\n*Nutrition\nInformation\nper 100g\nproduct (approx.)\nCarbohydrates 62g\n**Sugar 15g\nProtein 7.5g\nFat 19.6g\nSaturated fatty acids 9.5g\nMono unsaturated fatty acids 7.3g\nPoly unsaturated fatty acids 1.8g\nTrans fatty acids 0g\nCholesterol 0mg\nDietary fiber 9g\nEnergy 455kcal\n\nFigures based on calculated values-\n(Ref: NIN*, US FDA norm)", "score": 100, "grade": "S", "explanation": "This food product achieved an excellent Grade S (100/100). This indicates that its good sources of protein and dietary fiber helped it earn a high score, even though it also contains added sugars and refined flour.", "alternative": {"name": "Homemade Whole Wheat Atta Biscuits", "recipe": "1. Mix whole wheat flour with a little ghee and jaggery until crumbly. 2. Add a splash of milk to form a firm dough. 3. Roll out the dough and cut into biscuit shapes. 4. Bake until golden and crisp."}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Contains added sugars", "impact": -10}, {"reason": "Contains refined flour (Maida)", "impact": -10}, {"reason": "Good source of protein", "impact": 10}, {"reason": "Good source of dietary fiber", "impact": 10}]}, "5": {"id": "28bf78a4-bc4f-42bb-a1df-575d2466b302", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-24T05:13:38.534092", "corrected_text": "NUTRITION INFORMATION\nHONEY SOY CHICKEN FLAVOURED POTATO CHIPS\nSERVINGS PER PACKAGE: (6)\nSERVING SIZE: 25g PER SERVE PER 100g % DAILY INTAKE*\nPER SERVING\nENERGY 565kJ 2260kJ 6%\nPROTEIN 1.5g 5.9g 3%\nFAT - TOTAL 8.5g 33.9g 12%\n- SATURATED 3.9g 15.5g 16%\n- TRANS 0.0g 0.0g\n- POLYUNSATURATED 0.9g 3.4g\n- MONOUNSATURATED 3.8g 15.0g\nCHOLESTEROL 0.0mg 0.0mg\nCARBOHYDRATE - TOTAL 13.3g 53.1g 4%\n- SUGARS 1.0g 3.9g 1%\nDIETARY FIBRE 0.7g 2.7g 2%\nSODIUM 193mg 770mg 8%\nPOTASSIUM 338mg 1350mg\nAll values are considered averages unless otherwise indicated.\n*Percentage Daily Intakes are based on an average adult diet of 8700kJ.\nYour daily intakes may be higher or lower depending on your energy needs.\nINGREDIENTS: Potatoes, Vegetable Oil, Sugar, Salt, Glucose, Natural\nFlavours (Soy), Vegetable Extract, Maltodextrin, Honey Powder,\nDextrin, Corn Starch, Vegetable Powders (Onion, Garlic), Spice,\nColours (Caramel I, Paprika Extract).", "score": 80, "grade": "A", "explanation": "This product earned a good score of 80/100, a Grade A. The score was reduced by 20 points because its ingredients include multiple forms of added sugar. Using different types of added sugars can quickly increase the overall sugar content in a food.", "alternative": {"name": "Baked Masala Potato Chips", "recipe": "1. Slice potatoes very thinly. 2. Toss with a little oil, salt, and your favorite spices. 3. Spread on a baking sheet and bake at 180\u00b0C until crisp. 4. Cool completely and enjoy."}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Contains multiple forms of added sugar", "impact": -20}]}, "6": {"id": "11a1e1a6-3148-411c-bd7c-cf1647646d48", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-29T04:17:28.791499", "corrected_text": "carbonated water, sugar, colour (caramel e150d), acid (phosphoric acid), natural flavourings, caffeine flavouring,", "score": 90, "grade": "NOVA 1", "explanation": "Hello there! I'm EcoSaur!\n\nThis food is minimally processed (NOVA 1) with low sugar and sodium, which is supportive for managing blood sugar and overall health. Its low additive density and high transparency mean it's a clear and simple choice, aligning well with balanced snack guidelines.", "alternative": {"name": "Roasted Masala Makhana", "recipe": "1. Dry roast makhana (fox nuts) in a pan until crispy. 2. Add a touch of ghee or oil. 3. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, and chaat masala. 4. Toss well and enjoy as a crunchy snack.", "prep_time_mins": 15, "approx_cost_inr": 40}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Standard nutritional profile; aligns with standard daily snack balance guidelines", "impact": 0}]}, "7": {"id": "d2378dba-53ef-4547-adf7-039d78dadc64", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-29T04:29:17.926823", "corrected_text": "NUTRITION INFORMATION\nHONEY SOY CHICKEN FLAVOURED POTATO CHIPS\nSERVINGS PER PACKAGE: (6)\nSERVING SIZE: 25g PER SERVE PER 100g % DAILY INTAKE*\nPER SERVING\nENERGY 565kJ 2260kJ 6%\nPROTEIN 1.5g 5.9g 3%\nFAT - TOTAL 8.5g 33.9g 12%\n- SATURATED 3.9g 15.5g 16%\n- TRANS 0.0g 0.0g\n- POLYUNSATURATED 0.9g 3.4g\n- MONOUNSATURATED 3.8g 15.0g\nCHOLESTEROL 0.0mg 0.0mg\nCARBOHYDRATE - TOTAL 13.3g 53.1g 4%\n- SUGARS 1.0g 3.9g 1%\nDIETARY FIBRE 0.7g 2.7g 2%\nSODIUM 193mg 770mg 8%\nPOTASSIUM 338mg 1350mg\nAll values are considered averages unless otherwise indicated.\n*Percentage Daily Intakes are based on an average adult diet of 8700 kJ.\nYour daily intakes may be higher or lower depending on your energy needs.\nINGREDIENTS: Potatoes, Vegetable Oil, Sugar, Salt, Glucose, Natural\nFlavours (Soy), Vegetable Extract, Maltodextrin, Honey Powder,\nDextrin, Corn Starch, Vegetable Powders (Onion, Garlic), Spice,\nColours (Caramel I, Paprika Extract).", "score": 60, "grade": "NOVA 4", "explanation": "Hello! EcoSaur here to help you understand your food's scorecard.\n\nThis product is classified as ultra-processed (NOVA 4) due to refined base processing, and its moderate transparency means some ingredient details may be less clear. It features a low sugar load, which can be helpful for managing blood sugar, alongside a moderate sodium load. A medium density of additives is present in the formulation.", "alternative": {"name": "Homemade Air-Fried Potato Wafers", "recipe": "1. Slice potatoes paper-thin using a mandoline and soak in cold water.\n2. Drain, dry completely on a towel, and toss with minimal olive oil and sea salt.\n3. Air-fry at 160\u00b0C for 12-15 minutes, shaking occasionally until golden crisp.\n4. Sprinkle with a dash of chaat masala.", "prep_time_mins": 20, "approx_cost_inr": 15}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Product is classified as ultra-processed (NOVA 4) due to refined base processing", "impact": -15}]}, "8": {"id": "2c337c25-958c-455b-9a88-1c169d298a47", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-29T04:29:41.940356", "corrected_text": "NUTRITION INFORMATION\nHONEY SOY CHICKEN FLAVOURED POTATO CHIPS\nSERVINGS PER PACKAGE: (6)\nSERVING SIZE: 25g PER SERVE PER 100g % DAILY INTAKE*\nPER SERVING\nENERGY 565kJ 2260kJ 6%\nPROTEIN 1.5g 5.9g 3%\nFAT - TOTAL 8.5g 33.9g 12%\n- SATURATED 3.9g 15.5g 16%\n- TRANS 0.0g 0.0g\n- POLYUNSATURATED 0.9g 3.4g\n- MONOUNSATURATED 3.8g 15.0g\nCHOLESTEROL 0.0mg 0.0mg\nCARBOHYDRATE - TOTAL 13.3g 53.1g 4%\n- SUGARS 1.0g 3.9g 1%\nDIETARY FIBRE 0.7g 2.7g 2%\nSODIUM 193mg 770mg 8%\nPOTASSIUM 338mg 1350mg\nAll values are considered averages unless otherwise indicated.\n*Percentage Daily Intakes are based on an average adult diet of 8700 kJ.\nYour daily intakes may be higher or lower depending on your energy needs.\nINGREDIENTS: Potatoes, Vegetable Oil, Sugar, Salt, Glucose, Natural\nFlavours (Soy), Vegetable Extract, Maltodextrin, Honey Powder,\nDextrin, Corn Starch, Vegetable Powders (Onion, Garlic), Spice,\nColours (Caramel I, Paprika Extract).", "score": 60, "grade": "NOVA 4", "explanation": "This product is classified as NOVA 4, indicating it has undergone multiple processing steps, yet it offers a low sugar load, which is helpful for blood sugar management. It contains a moderate amount of sodium and a medium density of additives. Moderate transparency means some information about its ingredients is clear, while other details might be less apparent.", "alternative": {"name": "Homemade Air-Fried Potato Wafers", "recipe": "1. Slice potatoes paper-thin using a mandoline and soak in cold water.\n2. Drain, dry completely on a towel, and toss with minimal olive oil and sea salt.\n3. Air-fry at 160\u00b0C for 12-15 minutes, shaking occasionally until golden crisp.\n4. Sprinkle with a dash of chaat masala.", "prep_time_mins": 20, "approx_cost_inr": 15}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Product is classified as ultra-processed (NOVA 4) due to refined base processing", "impact": -15}]}, "9": {"id": "41646994-3088-4362-a53c-c1e88e870ab9", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-29T04:32:30.406943", "corrected_text": "Ingredients: Carbonated Water, High Fructose Corn Syrup, Caramel Color, Phosphoric Acid, Natural Flavors, Caffeine.", "score": 80, "grade": "NOVA 2", "explanation": "This product uses commonly processed ingredients (NOVA Group 2) with a low number of additives, offering high transparency to help you understand its content. Its low sugar and sodium loads are supportive for blood sugar management and align well with standard daily snack guidelines.", "alternative": {"name": "Traditional Nannari Sherbet", "recipe": "1. Mix 2 tablespoons of natural nannari (sarsaparilla) root syrup in chilled water.\n2. Add freshly squeezed lime juice.\n3. Stir well with crushed ice.\n4. Enjoy as a traditional body coolant with no synthetic colors or preservatives.", "prep_time_mins": 2, "approx_cost_inr": 12}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Standard nutritional profile; aligns with standard daily snack balance guidelines", "impact": 0}]}, "10": {"id": "71e49d5b-69d6-4256-b25c-d5ea414bbf84", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-29T04:33:10.883537", "corrected_text": "Ingredients: Carbonated Water, High Fructose Corn Syrup, Caramel Color, Phosphoric Acid, Natural Flavors, Caffeine.", "score": 80, "grade": "NOVA 2", "explanation": "Hello! This food has a NOVA Group 2 rating, meaning it uses familiar culinary ingredients with few additives. Its low sugar and sodium are positive features for those mindful of their intake, particularly for blood sugar balance. With high transparency, it provides a standard nutritional profile that fits well into daily snack guidelines.", "alternative": {"name": "Traditional Nannari Sherbet", "recipe": "1. Mix 2 tablespoons of natural nannari (sarsaparilla) root syrup in chilled water.\n2. Add freshly squeezed lime juice.\n3. Stir well with crushed ice.\n4. Enjoy as a traditional body coolant with no synthetic colors or preservatives.", "prep_time_mins": 2, "approx_cost_inr": 12}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Standard nutritional profile; aligns with standard daily snack balance guidelines", "impact": 0}]}, "11": {"id": "52c9092a-bae4-4f53-aabf-b24bc4046294", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-29T04:33:42.400246", "corrected_text": "Ingredients: Carbonated Water, High Fructose Corn Syrup, Caramel Color, Phosphoric Acid, Natural Flavors, Caffeine.", "score": 80, "grade": "NOVA 2", "explanation": "This food is minimally processed with low sugar and sodium, making it a generally suitable option for those managing blood sugar. Its low additive density and high transparency offer a clear and balanced choice that fits well within daily snack guidelines.", "alternative": {"name": "Traditional Nannari Sherbet", "recipe": "1. Mix 2 tablespoons of natural nannari (sarsaparilla) root syrup in chilled water.\n2. Add freshly squeezed lime juice.\n3. Stir well with crushed ice.\n4. Enjoy as a traditional body coolant with no synthetic colors or preservatives.", "prep_time_mins": 2, "approx_cost_inr": 12}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Standard nutritional profile; aligns with standard daily snack balance guidelines", "impact": 0}]}, "12": {"id": "98cf18f3-fcb4-4f6f-9ef0-466633d1fb92", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-29T04:35:14.610455", "corrected_text": "INGREDIENTS:\nREFINED WHEAT FLOUR (43%), WHOLE WHEAT\nFLOUR (20%), EDIBLE VEGETABLE OIL, SUGAR,\nWHEAT BRAN (4.7%), MILK SOLIDS, LIQUID\nGLUCOSE, CEREAL PRODUCTS, RAISING\nAGENTS [500(ii), 503(ii)], EDIBLE COMMON SALT,\nEMULSIFIERS [322, 472e, 471 & 481(i)], MALT\nEXTRACT AND DOUGH CONDITIONER (223).\n(Numbers in brackets as per International Numbering System)\nCONTAINS ADDED FLAVOURS -\n(ARTIFICIAL FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES -\nVANILLA, CEREAL & MILK)\n\nSTORE IN A COOL, HYGIENIC AND DRY PLACE.\nTRANSFER CONTENTS TO A CLEAN AND AIRTIGHT\nCONTAINER ONCE OPENED.\n\nhealth at www.ihealthu.com\nus at www.facebook.com/ihealthu\n\n*Nutrition\nInformation per 100g\nproduct (approx.)\nCarbohydrates 62g\n**Sugar 15g\nProtein 7.5g\nFat 19.6g\nSaturated fatty acids 9.5g\nMono unsaturated fatty acids 7.3g\nPoly unsaturated fatty acids 1.8g\nTrans fatty acids 0g\nCholesterol 0mg\nDietary fiber 9g\nEnergy 455kcal\n\nFigures based on calculated values -\n(Ref: \"NIN\" & US FDA norm)", "score": 90, "grade": "NOVA 1", "explanation": "This food is minimally processed with few additives, and its high transparency helps you understand what you're eating. Its low sugar and sodium content supports stable blood sugar and heart health, aligning well with balanced snack guidelines.", "alternative": {"name": "Homemade Air-Fried P