 Group of 1 suggests it's minimally processed, and the low additive density means it has few added ingredients. This makes it a good choice for balancing your daily snack intake.", "alternative": {"name": "Homemade Air-Fried Potato Wafers", "recipe": "1. Slice potatoes paper-thin using a mandoline and soak in cold water.\n2. Drain, dry completely on a towel, and toss with minimal olive oil and sea salt.\n3. Air-fry at 160\u00b0C for 12-15 minutes, shaking occasionally until golden crisp.\n4. Sprinkle with a dash of chaat masala.", "prep_time_mins": 20, "approx_cost_inr": 15}, "breakdown": [{"reason": "Standard nutritional profile; aligns with standard daily snack balance guidelines", "impact": 0}]}, "15": {"id": "14d690b9-145b-43e3-940d-004678cf0119", "user_id": "default", "date": "2026-05-29T04:47:20.148286", "corrected_text": "Ingredients: Rolled Oats (25.1%), Candied Fruit and Nut (24%)\n{Candied Cranberry (14%), Almonds (10%)}, Sugar, Oat Flour (10.7%),\nEdible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein), Rice (4.2%), Whole Wheat (3.9%),\nRice Flour (2.7%), Liquid Glucose, Corn Flour (1.8%), Honey, Malt Extract,\nWheat Bran (0.6%), Wheat Flour (0.5%), Iodized Salt, Dextrose,\nBarley Flour (0.1%), Vitamins, Raising Agent (INS 500ii),\nMinerals, Antioxidant (INS 320)\n\nCONTAINS ADDED FLAVOURS (NATURE IDENTICAL AND\nARTIFICIAL CREAM FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES)\nCONTAINS GLUTEN, ALMONDS.\nMAY CONTAIN TRACES OF SOY AND MILK.", "score": 90, "grade": "NOVA 1", "explanation": "This food is minimally processed, meaning it's closer to its natural state. It also has fewer additives, a low amount of sugar, and a low sodium content, which are generally good signs for a balanced snack. Its clear ingredient list helps you understand what you're eating, fitting well within typical daily snack recommendations.", "alternative": {"name": "Homemade Air-Fried Potato Wafers", "recipe": "1. Slice potatoes paper-thin using a mandoline and soak in cold water.\n2. Drain, dry completely on a towel, and toss wi